#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Today's topic is about teen safety.\n"
"\n"
"Teens can spend a lot of time outside the house or online, where it is harder for us to keep them safe.\n"
"\n"
"Talking together about safe and unsafe places, and how to prevent problems, really helps!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Why is teen safety important for you and your family?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Greetings, everyone.\n"
"\n"
"Today our topic is teen safety.\n"
"\n"
"It is our responsibility as parents to keep our teens safe at all times. We need to ensure that our teenagers are safe in the communities that we live in. It is our responsibility that we make them aware of the safe and unsafe areas in the communities.\n"
"\n"
"It is also our responsibility to ensure that they understand the dangers that they might be exposed to when they are online. That way our teenagers will be responsible and be able to make right decisions to keep themselves safe too."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Sometimes our teens know things about their environment that we might not realise - and by talking, we can learn how to support them better."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_female_8.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "A safety plan helped @data.characters.media_female_8.name protect her teen. Tap play to hear more"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"I was so grateful to make the safety plan with my teen. I thought I knew which areas are safe for my teen and which are not. But when we made the safety plan together, I realised that my girl knew more areas that I was not aware of.\n"
"\n"
"I also thought she was safe at school, but through this activity I realised she was being bullied and the teachers did not do anything about it.\n"
"\n"
"The more we talked, the more I understood and got information from my teen. That really helped me to protect my teen and keep her safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_mother.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name:
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"The most important way to help keep your teen safe is to make sure that they know they can talk to you about anything. \n"
"\n"
"You can also come up with a Safety Word - a simple word your teen can use to let you know they have a problem, without fear of you getting angry. \n"
"\n"
"Let's see how this worked for @data.characters.f1_mother.name and her daughter @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name:"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f2_daughter_19.name
#.      @data.characters.friend_female_1.name!
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Something happened when I was out with my friends @data.characters.f2_daughter_19.name and @data.characters.friend_female_1.name!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Tell me, @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Hey beautiful. I have been looking at you for a while. You are very beautiful, what is your name?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Her name is @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name, should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name, would you like to come with me to have something to drink and chips? Come on, get in, you will be back in time, I promise…"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I am not sure if that is a good idea…"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You are lucky, my friend. I wish a man would ask ME out and buy me gifts. I am telling you, if you do not do this I’m going to tell everyone you are stupid!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name do not go! Be careful! Let’s go home. It is dangerous to go with people you do not know. Besides, he is too old for you and what he is doing is wrong."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I just do not know…"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Pfff, I am so proud of you for not getting into the car. That was a dangerous situation, thank you for telling me!\n"
"\n"
"You can always call me or talk to me when something like this happens. We can even use a Safety Word, so I know something is wrong - and I promise I will not be angry."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name! should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Thank you, @data.characters.f1_mother.role_name! Our Safety Word could be ‘blue house’. I could call and say something like ‘I forgot my book at the blue house’ and you would know to come help me."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name. should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let's think about what happened to @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "What was risky about that situation?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "The man in the car was pressuring @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name with gifts"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name's should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "@data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name's friend was encouraging her"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Going with an older man puts @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name in a dangerous situation where she can get hurt or be forced to do things"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Many girls in our communities get pregnant or catch HIV from older men"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "There were no other trusted adults to advise @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"All those things are true! \n"
"\n"
"@data.characters.f1_daughter_16.name could have gotten into a dangerous situation if she had gotten into the car."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let's look at another example of a dangerous situation together."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "My friend has been talking with a guy our age online... She is going to send him photos of herself. Is that better because he is our age?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"You are a good friend for being worried about her. Sending sexy photos is a real risk too.\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes people are not who they say they are online – he could say he is your age but be a 50-year-old man. Or when they break up, he could send those photos to everyone and your friend would feel awful."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Things like that can happen to any teen, so  let's think about our teens' online safety."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "What do you think is the biggest online risk for teens these days?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Adults use social media, gaming and messaging apps and websites to meet teenagers and pressure them to do sexual things"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, this is a serious risk. Some adults may act friendly online but try to trick or pressure teens. Talking openly can help keep your teen safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "People post things online to make us hurt other people - like making violence seem cool or spreading hate towards certain races or countries"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, this is a real concern. Some people spread hate or make violence seem normal. Helping your teen think about what they see online can protect them."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "People put things online to convince teenagers to hurt themselves or take their own lives"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, sadly this does happen. Some online spaces can make teens feel hopeless or alone. Checking in often can help keep your teen safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Teenagers share sexy photos, videos or information about themselves, and others use it to embarrass or threaten them"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, this is a real danger. Once something is shared, it can be spread or used to hurt them. Teaching your teen to pause and think before sharing can make a big difference."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "People can often be nasty to teenagers online - they feel like they can bully people safely"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, online bullying happens a lot because people feel braver behind a screen. Talking about kindness and bullying can help your teen feel supported and know what to do."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"To keep our teens safe, we need to understand the dangerous situations they could get into! \n"
"\n"
"Let’s get practical now, and draw two maps of safe and unsafe places:\n"
"- 🗺️ A map of our community\n"
"- 🌐 A map of apps/websites we use online"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can you make these maps together with your family now?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes, my family can join in now"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let me try it out by myself"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Great! You will need a:\n"
"\n"
"- 📄 Piece of paper (or old newspaper or a cardboard box) \n"
"- 🖊️ Pen"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Step 1: Draw all the important places in your community."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Draw a map of your teen’s community, with pictures of all the main places like streets, your house, school, shops, places your teen visits."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Step 2: Choose which places are safe and unsafe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"- Which areas on your map are safe for teenagers? CIRCLE these\n"
"- Which areas on your map are unsafe for teenagers? CROSS those off\n"
"- What makes a place safe or unsafe?\n"
"- What could you and your teen do to keep your teen safer?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Step 3: Identify where you can get support."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Sometimes, we can find ourselves in trouble.\n"
"\n"
"- Where can you and your teen get support when you face a crisis? MARK those areas with a little object like a stone or piece of paper."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Step 4: Now recognise the risky places online and how you can make them safer."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"- Draw pictures of the apps and websites your teenagers use\n"
"- Recognise how good they are at using the web!\n"
"- Think about which ones might be unsafe. Why?\n"
"- What could you and your teen do to make using the internet safer for your teen and their friends?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Here are some skills to help you keep your teen safe!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "MAPS"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Make maps with your teen of safe and unsafe areas in your community and online. Talk about how to keep their information, photos and videos private online. Talk about how once something goes online, it stays there forever. They might know an example from their friends."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "RULES"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Make rules with your teen about how they can stay safe in your community (especially in risky areas that cannot be avoided), and how they can safely use the apps and websites that they like."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The following strings should not be translated: 
#.      @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name
#.      @data.characters.f1_mother.name,
#.      @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Remember how @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name and her mother, @data.characters.f1_mother.name, made a rule together to help @data.characters.f1_daughter_13.name have fun and stay safe online? It worked well because they made clear rules together in a calm and positive way!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "SAFETY WORD"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Agree on a Safety Word. If something happens that makes your teen upset, uncomfortable or scared, they can say the Safety Word and you will help them without getting angry or punishing them, even if they were doing something wrong."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "More tips"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"What Safety Word can you choose with your teen? Here are some ideas from other families:\n"
"\n"
"🥑 A specific food\n"
"👵🏽 A specific family member\n"
"🐒 A specific animal\n"
"🤔 Something else"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"If you have not done it together yet, this week's home assignment is to make two maps with your teen of safe and unsafe places:\n"
"\n"
"1) 🗺️ Map of your community\n"
"2) 🌐 Map of apps and websites your teen uses\n"
"\n"
"Make sure you are both happy with the safety plan. What really matters is that you talk with your teen as you do this – often teens know much more than we do about where it is safe and unsafe!"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Can you make a safety map with your teen and talk about ways to stay safe online and in your community?"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's great! Taking the time to map out safe and unsafe places together helps your teen feel more confident and supported."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "I think so"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "You can do it! Even starting the conversation is a big step towards helping your teen stay safe."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "That's okay. It can feel hard at first, but small talks about safety make a big difference. Try again when you feel ready."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "When teens know they can turn to us without fear, they are more likely to ask for help when something feels unsafe - both offline and online. Talking calmly and making safety plans together builds trust that lasts."
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
#. The string @data.characters.media_daughter_7.name should not be translated.
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Safety planning helped @data.characters.media_daughter_7.name open up. Hear her story"
msgstr ""

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When my friends or I got into trouble, I would always try to hide it from my mother because she would get so angry and shout at me.\n"
"\n"
"When we made the map of safe and unsafe places, I learnt a lot – also why it is dangerous to share every picture online. My mother told me I can always ask her if there is a problem and she promised she would not get mad.\n"
"\n"
"She kept her promise, so now if I have a problem or I do not feel safe I know we can always come up with a solution together. I can even talk to my mother about the things I do online now!"
msgstr ""
